
[1]inquiry

   INQUI'RY, n.

   1. The act of inquiring; a seeking for information by asking questions;
   interrogation.

   The men who were sent from Cornelius, had made inquiry for Simon's
   house,and stood before the gate. Acts.10.

   2. Search for truth, information or knowledge; research; examination
   into facts or principles by proposing and discussing questions, by
   solving problems, by experiments or other modes; as physical inquiries;
   inquiries about philosophical knowledge.

   The first inquiry of a rational being should be, who made me? the
   second, why was I made? who is my Creator, and what is his will?
